<h3 id="migration-notes-from-cosmos-44x">Migration Notes from COSMOS 4.4,x:</h3>

<p>To upgrade to the latest version of COSMOS, run ‚Äúbundle update cosmos‚Äù in your COSMOS project folder.</p>

<p>Modify you system.txt files to:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Make sure you have a X_CSRF_TOKEN line with a unique value (anything will do, just change it)</li>
  <li>Change all LISTEN_HOST settings to 127.0.01 unless you need connections from external hosts</li>
  <li>If you know only specific external hosts will be connecting, add ALLOW_ACCESS lines for each</li>
  <li>Only add ALLOW_ROUTER_COMMANDING if you are chaining CmdTlmServers (that need to send commands), or you are receiving commands through routers</li>
  <li>Only add ALLOW_ORIGIN &lt;Address of webpage&gt;if you expect COSMOS to be accessed from a webpage</li>
  <li>Add ALLOW_HOST <Your COSMOS="" IP="" Address="">:7777, etc if you expect the COSMOS APIs to be accessed from external computers. Otherwise it will only accept connections that have a HOST header set to localhost</Your></li>
</ol>
